&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Pharmacist Medicines Information, Governance and Safety – &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross site (based at QEH site)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic pharmacist who wishes to apply and develop their medicines information skills and knowledge in a dynamic and busy Medicines Information Centre. The Medicines Information Centre at Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust is one of only two Medicines Information centres in South East London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is based at the Queen Elizabeth Hospital in Woolwich, undertaking a wide range of local and regional activities. Responsibilities of this role will include providing a medicines enquiry answering service to staff, patients of Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust. This ranges from advising on complex patient-related clinical issues to producing evidence-based answers to queries, supporting patient safety, cost-effective prescribing and medicines optimisation. There will be opportunity to maintain regular clinical pharmacy practice. Continuing professional development and research are actively encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your main roles will be to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a deputy for the Lead Pharmacist in their absence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the day to day running of Medicines Information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To provide systematic training in MI skills to pre-registration students and junior staff rotating through MI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clinical services to a ward&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will ideally have at least two and half years post-registration experience in a hospital pharmacy environment. You will also hold a postgraduate qualification. Please see the Person Specification for further criteria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 3rd December via MS Teams&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please Note: &lt;/strong&gt;The Trust reserves the right to close the vacancy earlier if there is a high volume of applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ahadia Anwer, Lead Pharmacist Medicines Information, Governance &amp; Safety,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ahadia.anwer@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;020 8836 4654&lt;/p&gt;
